<skill name="toolFailureRecovery">
Use this skill whenever a tool call fails, returns malformed data, times out, or produces unexpected results.

First carefully inspect the full error message before taking another action.
Do not blindly retry the exact same call repeatedly.

Identify the likely failure category:
- invalid arguments
- formatting mistakes
- missing files or permissions
- environment issues
- temporary tool failure
- timeout or resource limits

Prefer the smallest possible correction before attempting larger changes.

If the issue may be temporary, retry conservatively.
If the issue is likely permanent, change strategy instead of looping.

When recovering from failure:
- preserve already completed work
- avoid undoing unrelated progress
- avoid making assumptions without evidence

If repeated recovery attempts fail, explain the limitation clearly to the user instead of continuing indefinitely.
</skill>